"title":{
"__html":"Hypercalcemia and Hyperparathyroidism"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"6472f0",
"children":[
"Hypercalcemia and Hyperparathyroidism"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s24_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0868da",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Primary hyperparathyroidism"
]
},
" is the most common cause of hypercalcemia in outpatients. Hypercalcemia is often discovered incidentally. Less common presentations are kidney stones, osteoporosis, pancreatitis, and fractures (osteoporosis). Hypercalcemia may also occur with the use of lithium (",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"parathyroid hormone",
"children":[
"PTH"
]
},
" mediated) or thiazide diuretics (non-PTH mediated) and in the setting of excessive ingestion of vitamin D and calcium."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"193cd5",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Malignancy"
]
},
" is the most common cause of hypercalcemia in hospitalized patients."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"45a8e4",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Sarcoidosis"
]
},
" may be associated with hypercalcemia (10% of patients) and hypercalciuria (50% of patients)."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_en_s24_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6ce44d",
"children":[
"Hypercalcemia requiring acute intervention is most often associated with a rapid rise in serum calcium level and serum calcium >14 mg/dL. Symptoms may include change in mental status and coma. It is most common in the setting of malignancy."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s24_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"fd254f",
"children":[
"If hypercalcemia is confirmed, check PTH, phosphate, creatinine, and 25-hydroxyvitamin D levels. If PTH is elevated or inappropriately normal in the setting of elevated serum calcium, the most likely cause is primary hyperparathyroidism."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"53b9ad",
"children":[
"In patients with hypercalcemia and normal PTH levels, measure urinary calcium excretion to exclude familial hypocalciuric hypercalcemia."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"37076d",
"children":[
"If hyperparathyroidism is confirmed and surgery is indicated, imaging may be indicated (ultrasound, sestamibi scan, CT, MRI)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f40a84",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Primary hyperparathyroidism is the most common manifestation of ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"multiple endocrine neoplasia type 1",
"children":[
"MEN1"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s24_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"10cf05",
"children":[
"For severe, symptomatic hypercalcemia, select:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b43eb4",
"children":[
"volume resuscitation with 0.9% saline"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"14bbae",
"children":[
"IV bisphosphonates"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"8efed2",
"children":[
"oral glucocorticoid therapy (if caused by multiple myeloma, B-cell lymphoma, or sarcoidosis)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c498bf",
"children":[
"Parathyroidectomy is indicated for patients with primary hyperparathyroidism and hypercalcemic complications, such as kidney stones, bone disease, or previous episodes of hypercalcemic crisis."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a7d077",
"children":[
"Asymptomatic patients are surgical candidates if they have any of the following:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9f5830",
"children":[
"serum calcium level >1 mg/dL above the upper limit of normal"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"58621f",
"children":[
"creatinine clearance <60 mL/min"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"3418a4",
"children":[
"T-score <−2.5 or vertebral fracture"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"11e37a",
"children":[
"age <50 years"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"29d577",
"children":[
"Watch for a precipitous fall in the serum calcium level caused by relative hypoparathyroidism after parathyroidectomy (“hungry bone” syndrome). Monitor serum calcium after surgery, and give oral calcium if mild hypocalcemia develops."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8004c3",
"children":[
"Treat patients who are not candidates for parathyroidectomy with cinacalcet or bisphosphonates."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"da0173",
"children":[
"Loop diuretics are not recommended in the treatment of hypercalcemia unless kidney failure or ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"heart failure",
"children":[
"HF"
]
},
" is present, in which case, volume expansion should precede the administration of loop diuretics to avoid hypotension and further kidney injury."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s24_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9c53b9",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 44-year-old man has a 1-year history of fatigue and poor concentration. His serum calcium level is 10.9 mg/dL, serum phosphorus level is 2.8 mg/dL, and PTH level is 75 pg/mL."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7ea235",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose primary hyperparathyroidism and measure serum vitamin D levels. For management, select parathyroidectomy."
]
}
]
}
]
